ical and Health Informatics  After You Apply      After You Apply  You’ve applied and submitted your application. Now what?      What's next?   You can check your application status online at any time. This will show you a checklist of all your items and let you know if they’re correct and complete.     Graduate application status    Personal interview  Personal interviews are by invitation only.   Departmental review  The time that it takes for an application to go through the review process varies. All elements submitted as part of your application are reviewed to gain a picture of you as a potential student, so the sooner you get all elements in, the sooner your application can be reviewed. After we complete our review of your application, we communicate recommendations and denials to Admissions.   Graduate college review  All admissions decisions recommended by the department must be approved and finalized by Admission and the Graduate College. The Graduate College may decide to uphold our recommendation or deny the application.   When you'll hear from us  Once Admissions enters a decision, your application status updates online and a letter is mailed to you.The official letter of acceptance comes from the Office of Admissions, not from our department  Visit your online application status page frequently for updates.      After a decision has been made   If you've been admitted...  Congratulations! Access our Admitted Student page for your next steps.  International students: If you’ll need a student visa, you should submit OIS financial documents through the application checklist for the Office of International Services. Contact the OIS concerning document requests and visa processing.   If you need to defer admission...  Admission can be deferred once for up to one academic year (for example, Fall admission can be deferred to the following Fall term). Notify us as soon as possible that you’d like to defer admission. If your deferral is approved, we’ll forward it to campus for final approval and official updates to the student record.   If you've been denied...  You may contact us directly to inquire about our decision. In some cases, we can advise you on what you can do to improve your applicant profile or successfully apply for a future term.            Questions?   We’re here to help. Get in touch with Harry Rhodes, program director, with any post-application questions.    You can contact Harry at:     Email  applyuicphdbhi@uic.edu      Phone  312-996-1445      Address  1919 W. Taylor St. 250 AHSB (MC 530) Chicago, IL 60612               Biomedical and Health Information Sciences    Back to main content           Admissions and Programs    Expand Admissions and Programs menu          BS in Health Information Management    Expand BS in Health Information Management menu          What to Expect    Before You Apply    Applying    Expand Applying menu          Transferring from another UIC program      After You Apply      Minor in Life Science Visualization    Expand Minor in Life Science Visualization menu          What to Expect    Applying      MS in Biomedical Visualization    Expand MS in Biomedical Visualization menu          What to Expect    Before You Apply    Applying    After You Apply    Meet Our Students    Expand Meet Our Students menu          Class of 2020    Class of 2021        MS in Health Informatics    PhD in Biomedical and Health Informatics    Expand PhD in Biomedical and Health Informatics menu          What to Expect    Before You Apply    Applying    After You Apply    Faculty      Post-Baccalaureate Certificate in Health Information Management    Post-Master’s Certificate in Health Informatics    Post-Baccalaureate Certificate in Health Informatics      News    Calendar    Directory    Contact                College of  Applied Health  Sciences       UI Health Logo                            Quick Links    Calendar    Directory    News    Inside AHS    Graduation      Resources    Academic Suppo